\f0\b What
\f1\b0  
\f0\b "Adams"
\f1\b0  
\f0\b most
\f1\b0  
\f0\b likely
\f1\b0  
\f0\b means:
\f1\b0 \
       In early American naming practice, particularly in the Upper South and\
       border states, a woman's maiden name (especially the mother's family\
       name) was often given as a middle name. "Adams" was likely her mother\
       Lydia (Butler) Million's family surname or a maternal grandparent's name\
        passed down. An alternative \'97 a prior marriage \'97 is less likely given\
       that she married at approximately age 20 and the marriage record gives\
       her surname simply as "Million."\
\
       
