\f1\b0  \'97 the same county and approximate time as Stephen's birth\
       (~1790, Amherst, Virginia). This puts Christopher's family in Amherst,\
       VA during the period when Stephen would have been born.\
       2. Christopher ended his days in 
\f0\b Lawrence
\f1\b0  
\f0\b County,
\f1\b0  
\f0\b Illinois
\f1\b0 , just east of\
        Clay County \'97 the same general region where Stephen settled. This is\
       geographic proximity consistent with family members following each\
       other.\
       3. The broader Coy family (John Coy Sr., John Jr., Daniel Coy, William\
       Coy) had a documented presence in 
\f0\b Nelson
\f1\b0  
\f0\b County,
\f1\b0  
\f0\b Kentucky
\f1\b0  by the\
       1780s\'961787 (per the tithables list), and the family moved through\
       Maryland \uc0\u8594  Virginia (Nelson/Amherst) \u8594  Kentucky \u8594  Illinois in exactly\
       the pattern observed for Stephen.\
       4. The Anthony Coy household in 
