\f0\b Bottom
\f1\b0  
\f0\b line
\f1\b0  
\f0\b on
\f1\b0  
\f0\b the
\f1\b0  
\f0\b parentage
\f1\b0  
\f0\b question:
\f1\b0  The Christopher Coy connection is\
        plausible and geographically coherent \'97 Christopher was in Amherst, VA\
       around Stephen's birth, had other children born in Amherst, and died in\
       adjacent Lawrence County, IL. But it remains unconfirmed by primary\
       documents. The more important uncertainty is whether the Amherst Coys\
       were the same family as the Maryland/Revolutionary War Coy line, or a\
       separate Coy family in Virginia. To confirm, you would need:\
       - Christopher Coy's Virginia land or court records from Amherst County\
       (~1785\'961800)\
       - Christopher Coy's pension file from the National Archives (NARA series\
        M804) \'97 it may list children by name\
       - An Amherst County deed or court record naming Stephen Coy with a\
       parent\
